  "commentary": "With SPX at 6597.46 sitting just below the max positive gamma strike at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell rallies into that level while providing support around the negative gamma zone at 6580. The PIN regime with 10.1B in total GEX creates a stabilizing environment where any move toward 6605 faces increasing dealer selling pressure, while dips toward 6580 trigger dealer buying that should limit downside. Watch for mean reversion between these bounds, with the 6686 flip strike acting as the upper boundary where regime shifts from stabilizing to amplifying.\n\nBottom line: expect price to stay pinned between 6580-6605 with limited breakout potential.",
